name: glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+]
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: The enzyme catalyses a step of the pentose phosphate pathway. The enzyme from the Gram-positive bacterium Leuconostoc mesenteroides prefers NADP+ while the enzyme from the Gram-negative bacterium Gluconacetobacter xylinus prefers NAD+. cf. EC 1.1.1.49, glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (NADP+) and EC 1.1.1.388, glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (NAD+).
